  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fresh Water Wells &amp; Hygiene Education in Wau</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water for South Sudan (WFSS) regularly provides WASH services during the dry season (December-May) in South Sudan. Operating in remote villages in the Bahr el Ghazal season necessitates closing the season in May as the rains make many areas inaccessible and our trucks and equipment cannot risk getting stuck. We are piloting a short summer season near our compound in Wau to provide additional services, and to use as a training opportunity for WFSS team members.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water for South Sudan will drill eight (8) borehole wells and provide hygiene education at sites around the city of Wau. Although Wau is the second largest city, with an estimated population of 150,000, there is limited infrastructure, and no piped water available. WFSS will install wells to serve local communities within Wau.</narrative>
  </description>
